commit.message:
VERSION: bump to v0.5.2

Update VERSION file to v0.5.2

include: fix typo in header files #error directive

Fix and rephrase #error directive in C++ header files

map: don't penalize failed ops

Don't penalize failed insert/erase/find operations on maps due to
branch prediction

str: add cdada_str_ncmp/cdada_str_ncmp_c

This commit adds support to compare (strcmp/strncmp) two cdada
strings or a cdada string and a regular C string.

It also adds test coverage.

src: revert use gen-srcs to autogen switch cases

Revert the use of gen-srcs

CHANGELOG|VERISON: update CHANGELOG, bump v0.5.0

Update CHANGELOG and bump v0.5.0

map: find() allow val=NULL check key presence

Allow to pass NULL in map_find() to only check presence of a key

list: use std::advance for cdada_list_get()

Simplify (and make more efficient?) list_get() using std::advance
instead of a manual loop.

map: add new feature map_get_pos

This commit adds the get_pos() feature into the map data stucture.
get_pos() allows to retrieve the Nth (pos) element of map, the same
way you would get as begin()+pos.

set: add new feature set_get_pos

This commit adds the get_pos() feature into the set data stucture.
get_pos() allows to retrieve the Nth (pos) element of set, the same
way you would get as begin()+pos.

CHANGELOG|VERISON: update CHANGELOG, bump v0.4.1

Update CHANGELOG and bump v0.4.1

set: fix ret values for first/last

Fix error path return values for set_first()/set_last()

include/__set_internal.h: minor copy&paste struct

Remove incorrect name of variable in op function definition, as a
result of copy&paste from map code. Not affecting running code.

ci: update to Ubuntu 22.04

This commit:

* Moves base image to Ubuntu 22.04, since 18.04 is no longer supported
  by actions
* It uses containers to build with old containers (e.g. using 18.04)

Signed-off-by: Paolo Lucente <pl+github@pmacct.net>
Signed-off-by: Marc Sune <marcdevel@gmail.com>

src: use gen-srcs to autogen switch cases

Use python3 jinja2 templating engine to autogen switch cases for
the default container support 1-256 bytes, so that we can easily
add larger types without having to manually copy&paste.

VERSION|CHANGELOG: prepare v0.4.0 entries

Prepare VERSION and CHANGELOG for v0.4.0 by adding
cdada_map_insert_replace()

map.h: add map_insert_replace()

Add an new API to insert or replace an existing element. This
change doesn't change the ABI.

configure.ac: fix valgrind detection (make check)

Fix valgrind detection so that `make check` doesn't fail when
valgrind is not installed in the system.

configure.ac: add --without-tests/examples

Add configure options `--without-tests` and `--without-examples`
to speed up builds. Default for both is "with".

CHANGELOG updated accordingly.

CHANGELOG: add entry for fixes in E_EMPTY

Update CHANGELOG with entry for `E_EMPTY` fixes

* cdada_map_last()

Make sure that E_EMPTY is return instead of E_NOT_FOUND, according
